● Job starts
● Job is moved to Completed state/queue
● Job queue is modified - data for active job is reported again when a change is made to the Pending/Active queue or the Completed queue (say submitting a job)
Printer also sends up Notifications where there are changes.

HydraClient requests GET_ENGINE_STATE data:
● Once an hour
All response data is sent to adapter.

Printer also sends up notifications where there are changes. Only changes are sent to the adapter.

0 = INIT, 1 = PRE_WARMUP, 2 = MECH_INIT, 3 = WARMUP, 4 = READY, 5 = PRINT, 6 = LOW_POWER, 7 = SLEEP, 8 = RECOVERY, 9 = MECH_CMD, 10 = DIAGS, 11 = SHELL, 12 = PAUSE, 13 = SHUTDOWN
